        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 6:24PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 624 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
New London, or 6 miles south of Kilgore, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Longview, Kilgore, White Oak, New London, Lakeport, Rolling
Meadows, Laird Hill and Monroe.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
